.NET Framework 3.5.name: OptitrackStreamingClient
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: Connects to a NatNet streaming server and makes the data available in lightweight Unity-friendly representations.

fields.name: m_frameDataUpdateLock
fields.summary: Lock held during access to fields which are potentially modified by NativeFrameReceivedEventArgs) (which executes on a separate thread). Note while the lock is held, any frame updates received are simply dropped.

fields.name: m_latestRigidBodyStates
fields.summary: Maps from a streamed rigid body's ID to its most recent available pose data.

fields.name: m_latestSkeletonStates
fields.summary: Maps from a streamed skeleton's ID to its most recent available pose data.

methods.name: FindDefaultClient()
methods.summary: Returns the first OptitrackStreamingClient component located in the scene. Provides a convenient, sensible default in the common case where only a single client exists. Issues a warning if more than one such component is found.
methods.returns: An arbitrary OptitrackClient from the scene, or null if none are found.

methods.name: GetLatestRigidBodyState(Int32 rigidBodyId)
methods.summary: Get the most recently received state for the specified rigid body.
methods.returns: The most recent available state, or null if none available.

params.value: Corresponds to the "User ID" field in Motive.

methods.name: GetLatestSkeletonState(Int32 skeletonId)
methods.summary: Get the most recently received state for the specified skeleton.
methods.returns: The most recent available state, or null if none available.

params.value: Taken from the corresponding Id field. To find the appropriate skeleton definition, use String).

methods.name: GetOrCreateRigidBodyState(Int32 rigidBodyId)
methods.summary: Returns the OptitrackRigidBodyState corresponding to the provided rigidBodyId. If the requested state object does not exist yet, it will initialize and return a newly-created one.
methods.remarks: Makes the assumption that the lock on m_frameDataUpdateLock is already held.
methods.returns: The existing state object, or a newly created one if necessary.

params.value: The ID of the rigid body for which to retrieve the corresponding state.

methods.name: GetOrCreateSkeletonState(Int32 skeletonId)
methods.summary: Returns the OptitrackSkeletonState corresponding to the provided skeletonId. If the requested state object does not exist yet, it will initialize and return a newly-created one.
methods.remarks: Makes the assumption that the lock on m_frameDataUpdateLock is already held.
methods.returns: The existing state object, or a newly created one if necessary.

params.value: The ID of the skeleton for which to retrieve the corresponding state.

methods.name: GetSkeletonDefinitionByName(string skeletonAssetName)
methods.summary: Retrieves the definition of the skeleton with the specified asset name.
methods.returns: The specified skeleton definition, or null if not found.

params.value: The name of the skeleton for which to retrieve the definition.

methods.name: OnDisable()
methods.summary: Disconnects from the streaming server and cleans up m_client.

methods.name: OnEnable()
methods.summary: (Re)initializes m_client and connects to the configured streaming server.

methods.name: OnNatNetFrameReceived(object sender, NativeFrameReceivedEventArgs eventArgs)
methods.summary: Event handler for NatNet frame delivery. Updates our simplified state representations. NOTE: This executes in the context of the NatNetLib network service thread!
methods.remarks: Because the sFrameOfMocapData type is expensive to marshal, we instead utilize the NativeFramePointer, treating it as as opaque, and passing it to some helper "accessor" functions to retrieve the subset of data we care about, using only blittable types which do not cause any garbage to be allocated.
methods.syntax: private void OnNatNetFrameReceived(object sender, NativeFrameReceivedEventArgs eventArgs)
methods.linkedSyntax: private void OnNatNetFrameReceived(object sender, NativeFrameReceivedEventArgs eventArgs)

methods.name: UpdateDefinitions()
methods.summary: Request data descriptions from the host, then update our definitions.

exceptions.value: Thrown by GetDataDescriptions if the request to the server fails.
